{"source_hash": "47cd46c373e7a095", "candidate": {"id": "cand-022", "name": "Yuki Tanaka", "raw_cv": "YUKI TANAKA\nyuki.tanaka@email.com | London, UK\n\nSOFTWARE ENGINEER \u2014 FULL STACK\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nFull-stack software engineer with 5 years of experience at high-growth consumer and B2B SaaS startups. Expert in TypeScript, React, and Node.js. Strong product intuition and experience working directly with design and product teams in fast-paced environments.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSoftware Engineer \u2014 Loom (Atlassian), London/Remote (2022\u2013present)\n- Build and maintain the video capture and playback pipeline (TypeScript, React, WebRTC)\n- Led migration of the editor component library to a new design system, reducing bundle size 30%\n- Own the sharing and permissions features; shipped public link expiry and watermarking\n- Part of the on-call rotation for the video delivery infrastructure\n\nSoftware Engineer \u2014 Pento (acquired by Deel), London (2020\u20132022)\n- Full-stack engineer on the payroll calculation engine (Node.js, TypeScript, PostgreSQL)\n- Built the tax table update pipeline reducing manual compliance work from 2 days to 2 hours\n- Introduced E2E testing with Playwright across the critical payroll flow\n\nJunior Software Engineer \u2014 Cleo AI, London (2019\u20132020)\n- Built React Native features for the Cleo personal finance app\n\nSKILLS\nTypeScript, JavaScript, React, React Native, Node.js, PostgreSQL, Redis, GraphQL, REST, WebRTC, Docker, Playwright, Jest, GitHub Actions\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Computer Science \u2014 King's College London (2016\u20132019)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish-Japanese dual citizen, UK right to work", "raw_linkedin": "Full-stack engineer who cares as much about the product as the code. Five years building features at startups that people actually use \u2014 Cleo, Pento, and now Loom. I'm strongest in TypeScript across the stack, and I've become particularly interested in real-time and multimedia web features. I enjoy working close to product and design, and I have a habit of flagging UX problems that haven't been filed as bugs yet. Looking for a senior full-stack or product engineer role at a growth-stage B2B or consumer tech company. London-based, prefer hybrid.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Hi Yuki, thanks for coming in. Can you tell me about the video pipeline work at Loom?\n\nYuki: Sure. The capture pipeline is TypeScript on both ends \u2014 React for the browser-side capture interface and a Node.js service for processing and delivery. The interesting technical challenge is that WebRTC-captured video varies a lot in quality depending on the client environment, so we do adaptive processing on ingest. I've been working on reducing the latency between finishing a recording and the video being shareable, which is the key UX metric for us.\n\nInterviewer: What's your approach to testing?\n\nYuki: I believe in testing at the right level. Unit tests for pure logic, integration tests for API contracts, and E2E for the critical user paths. At Pento I introduced Playwright for E2E testing because the payroll calculation flow is mission-critical \u2014 if that's broken, companies can't pay their employees. We had three incidents in my first month that could have been caught by E2E tests, so I pushed for it and got it shipped within a quarter.\n\nInterviewer: This role is predominantly backend Node/TypeScript. How do you feel about moving away from frontend work?\n\nYuki: Honestly, that's part of the appeal. I enjoy the full-stack context but I want to go deeper on backend \u2014 distributed systems, reliability, API design at scale. I feel like I've hit the ceiling of what I can learn on the frontend side and the backend problems are more interesting to me right now.\n\nInterviewer: Salary expectations?\n\nYuki: I'm at \u00a382,000. I'd be looking for \u00a388\u201395,000.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["TypeScript", "JavaScript", "React", "React Native", "Node.js", "PostgreSQL", "Redis", "GraphQL", "REST", "WebRTC", "Docker", "Playwright", "Jest", "GitHub Actions"], "industries": ["SaaS", "FinTech", "EdTech"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.82, "constraints": [{"id": "78165017", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a382,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 82000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "1d31796a", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation range \u00a388,000\u2013\u00a395,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 88000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "329f0275", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation upper bound \u00a395,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "8693c057", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "London-based, prefers hybrid working arrangement", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": "London, hybrid", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}, {"id": "acd3caaf", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_type", "description": "Interested in moving deeper into backend work \u2014 distributed systems, reliability, and API design at scale", "canonical_key": null, "value": "backend-focused", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "d8fe08ae", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "company_profile", "description": "Seeking senior full-stack or product engineer role at growth-stage B2B or consumer tech company", "canonical_key": null